name: Facescapes_02
description: by Linn Phyllis Seeger - “Facescapes“ focuses primarily on the tensions between possession and freedom, repetition and singularity. Through the extreme fragmentation of her body, Seeger consciously plays with the notion of collectability. The collector of this work can now acquire a terrain or fragment of the artist and thus, own her. The material and immaterial identity is crushed, distributed and circulated until it develops a life of its own. The owner also becomes a part of Seeger's terrain.
